WEBVTT

00:06.900 --> 00:09.230
[ Down-tempo music plays ]

00:21.430 --> 00:23.670
[ Freewheel clicking ]

00:36.270 --> 00:38.700
[ Baby cooing ]

00:45.370 --> 00:47.630
[ Up-tempo music plays ]

00:51.630 --> 00:53.130
Jordan?

00:55.100 --> 00:57.170
[ Dog barking in distance ]

01:05.430 --> 01:07.270
[ Door closes ]

01:11.030 --> 01:13.900
[ Up-tempo music plays ]

01:31.030 --> 01:32.900
MANDY:
In all honesty,

01:32.900 --> 01:35.930
a school like this, a blended
school in a place like this,

01:35.930 --> 01:36.900
doesn´t work.

01:36.900 --> 01:39.270
Everybody said that.
Everybody thought that.

01:39.270 --> 01:40.900
But I can´t tell you
how many people

01:40.900 --> 01:43.130
thought this place
was going to be a failure.

01:43.130 --> 01:45.900
And yet here we are,
making it a success.

01:47.130 --> 01:48.900
You´re late, Mr. Bell.

01:49.500 --> 01:50.970
Traffic.

01:50.970 --> 01:52.230
Sign´s here.

01:52.230 --> 01:54.530
Oh, great.
Let´s have a look.

01:54.530 --> 01:58.170
Bottom line is we need parents
to sign their kids up today.

01:58.170 --> 01:58.900
Why?

01:58.900 --> 02:02.400
Well, yes, for finance, for
governors, and for the council.

02:02.400 --> 02:04.800
But let´s do it for us, eh?

02:04.800 --> 02:07.930
Let´s do it for the future
not only of this school,

02:07.930 --> 02:09.900
but for the future
of the whole town.

02:12.470 --> 02:13.700
Good, no?

02:13.700 --> 02:15.300
Yeah!

02:15.300 --> 02:18.030
Ackley Bridge Collage.

02:23.470 --> 02:25.900
[ Mid-tempo music plays ]

02:29.670 --> 02:32.630
Were you drinking
when you drew this picture?

02:32.630 --> 02:33.900
Does everyone know about it?

02:33.900 --> 02:35.430
You can´t do nothing
in Ackley Bridge.

02:35.430 --> 02:36.970
Everyone know what you´re up to.

02:36.970 --> 02:38.900
And don´t you teach my Razia
any tricks.

02:38.900 --> 02:40.630
She got bloody plenty
of her own.

02:40.630 --> 02:41.900
If she came home a drunk,

02:41.900 --> 02:44.270
I won´t be as good
as your mother were, you know.

02:49.700 --> 02:50.900
People up North.

02:51.970 --> 02:53.530
Were you all right
after your party?

02:53.530 --> 02:55.230
Haven´t seen you all week.

02:55.230 --> 02:58.470
Chloe, what have I said
about this?

02:58.470 --> 02:59.930
It´s for the Open Day.

02:59.930 --> 03:01.100
I don´t care.

03:01.100 --> 03:04.000
You can do the English
presentation with me instead.

03:05.230 --> 03:07.300
I´m not meant to see you,
apparently.

03:07.300 --> 03:09.370
EMMA: Think yourself lucky
to be here at all, Jordan.

03:09.370 --> 03:10.630
I had a good mind
to ring your dad.

03:10.630 --> 03:11.770
What?

03:11.770 --> 03:13.630
-Let him know what went on.
-Mum.

03:13.630 --> 03:16.170
Chloe.
Now.

03:16.170 --> 03:18.130
[ Down-tempo music plays ]

03:18.130 --> 03:20.070
It weren´t my fault.

03:20.070 --> 03:21.730
So all the governors
will be here,

03:21.730 --> 03:26.170
and, uh, we´ll have loads
of prospective parents, we hope.

03:26.170 --> 03:29.070
Um, so, please, just everybody
on their best behavior,

03:29.070 --> 03:31.770
and, uh, let´s just, um...

03:32.370 --> 03:34.900
...let´s just make a success
of today.

03:35.500 --> 03:37.530
Got a minute?

03:37.530 --> 03:38.770
See that?

03:38.770 --> 03:39.770
They split up,

03:39.770 --> 03:42.900
but they´ve still got to keep it
up for the sake of the kids.

03:43.470 --> 03:44.570
I don´t know why you lot

03:44.570 --> 03:46.670
are so interested
in your teachers´ private lives.

03:46.670 --> 03:48.530
You´d think you´d have
more important things to do.

03:48.530 --> 03:50.930
[ Indistinct conversations ]

03:53.100 --> 03:54.470
RIZ:
He´s got no shame.

03:54.470 --> 03:56.430
Mrs. Carter and Mr. Bell´s
bust-up --

03:56.430 --> 03:58.170
like that´s naught to do
with him.

03:59.730 --> 04:02.200
[ Down-tempo music plays ]

04:04.170 --> 04:05.900
Dad?
You got my speech?

04:05.900 --> 04:06.900
Yeah.

04:07.630 --> 04:09.230
I looked over it.

04:09.230 --> 04:10.570
A bit sloppy for you.

04:11.900 --> 04:12.900
Got distracted.

04:12.900 --> 04:14.970
What distracted you?
Better not be a boy.

04:14.970 --> 04:16.730
No.

04:17.270 --> 04:18.900
You´re a good girl, aren´t you?

04:20.100 --> 04:21.070
Mrs. Carter,

04:21.070 --> 04:22.900
do you want me to pop out front
to meet the parents?

04:22.900 --> 04:24.770
Yeah. Yeah.
Okay.

04:28.070 --> 04:30.130
[ Whispering ]
Someone´s feeling the pressure.

04:34.670 --> 04:38.170
[ Indistinct conversations ]

04:38.170 --> 04:40.530
Also I´ve got, um,
Jordan Wilson and Chloe Voyle

04:40.530 --> 04:41.530
down in art.

04:41.530 --> 04:42.630
Is that a good idea?

04:42.630 --> 04:44.270
They´re hardly model students,
are they?

04:44.270 --> 04:46.170
Do you want me to change them,
Mrs. Carter?

04:46.700 --> 04:47.900
Stop it, Steve.

04:49.670 --> 04:50.730
Look, the kid´s good at art.

04:50.730 --> 04:52.430
I mean, how much damage
can he do in the canteen

04:52.430 --> 04:54.170
with a couple of paintings?

04:54.170 --> 04:56.100
[ Down-tempo music plays ]

04:57.900 --> 05:00.430
Oi. Stranger.

05:01.400 --> 05:03.100
What you doing here?

05:03.100 --> 05:04.800
Jamie will be older next year.

05:04.800 --> 05:06.030
Thought I´d see
about coming back.

05:06.030 --> 05:08.130
-Would you like that?
-What do you mean?

05:09.170 --> 05:11.930
Us -- like together, in school.

05:12.530 --> 05:15.070
You could look after him in your
frees when you´re in sixth form.

05:18.030 --> 05:19.730
Why would I want to do that?

05:19.730 --> 05:21.930
Why would I look after
someone else´s kid?

05:22.500 --> 05:23.470
What?

05:23.470 --> 05:26.470
I´ve one a DNA test.
He´s not mine, Candice.

05:27.770 --> 05:28.900
You got a DNA test?

05:28.900 --> 05:30.900
All that guilt you put me on
about not seeing him

05:30.900 --> 05:32.330
and he´s not even mine.

05:33.230 --> 05:34.300
Are you sure?

05:34.300 --> 05:35.970
Am I the only one
whose name you can remember?

05:35.970 --> 05:37.070
I´m not like that.

05:37.070 --> 05:38.270
My dad told me.
Everyone told me.

05:38.270 --> 05:39.530
I just didn´t listen.

05:39.530 --> 05:42.030
I really wanted you to be
the dad. I thought --

05:42.030 --> 05:43.770
Why are you acting like you
like me all of a sudden?

05:43.770 --> 05:45.230
I´ve always liked you.

05:45.230 --> 05:48.900
You liked my brother,
just like all the girls.

05:48.900 --> 05:51.670
That´s why you hung around
with us, so you could see him.

05:51.670 --> 05:53.500
We only did it the once.

05:54.030 --> 05:55.570
-What?
-What´d he tell you?

05:55.570 --> 05:57.070
´Cause it was only once.

05:57.070 --> 05:58.670
He´s the only other person
I´ve been with,

05:58.670 --> 06:00.830
and he didn´t even talk to me
after.

06:00.830 --> 06:02.100
You were really nice.

06:02.100 --> 06:03.230
Who?

06:04.200 --> 06:05.730
You talking about Cory?

06:06.170 --> 06:07.570
Leave -- Leave it, Jordan,
´cause --

06:07.570 --> 06:09.530
My brother Cory?

06:10.670 --> 06:13.970
And this is one
of our science classrooms.

06:13.970 --> 06:16.170
And this is Ms. Shariff.

06:16.900 --> 06:18.900
You gonna come say hello,
Ms. Shariff?

06:18.900 --> 06:21.370
Hiya.
We´re learning about catalysts.

06:21.370 --> 06:23.770
We´re big believers here
in practicals.

06:23.770 --> 06:28.100
Hands-on experimentation
with students is encouraged.

06:30.330 --> 06:32.900
-Um, please...
-[ Indistinct shouting ]

06:32.900 --> 06:33.700
Miss.

06:33.700 --> 06:35.430
-Uh, sorry.
-[ Laughter ]

06:35.430 --> 06:37.500
GIRL:
I don´t know what I did wrong.

06:37.500 --> 06:40.230
Right. Shall we, uh,
move on to the next class?

06:40.230 --> 06:43.130
[ Mid-tempo music plays ]

06:43.130 --> 06:44.730
You´re just a liar, Candice.
That´s what you are.

06:44.730 --> 06:47.430
Don´t talk to her like that.
I´ll give you a bloody thumping.

06:47.430 --> 06:50.230
You´re a joke, Candice, a stupid
girl who got knocked up.

06:50.230 --> 06:51.300
You get out.
Go.

06:51.300 --> 06:52.530
-Go.
-Don´t touch me.

06:52.530 --> 06:53.570
-Here, Jordan.
-KANEEZ: Shame on you.

06:53.570 --> 06:55.170
Don´t worry. Don´t worry.
I´ll sort him.

06:55.170 --> 06:57.570
You´ll sort me, will you?
It´s all right. Mr. Bell´s here.

06:57.570 --> 06:58.900
Oi.
Come to Ackley Bridge.

06:58.900 --> 07:01.970
Get taught by a hero --
Mr. Steven Bell.

07:01.970 --> 07:03.830
Um, have I not done enough
for you, kid?

07:03.830 --> 07:05.570
-Come on. Don´t show me up.
-Oh, yeah.

07:05.570 --> 07:06.770
You´ve done loads for me.

07:06.770 --> 07:09.530
Hiding my baby around school,
putting me on the rugby team.

07:09.530 --> 07:11.170
Absolute star he is.

07:11.170 --> 07:12.570
I´ve put my neck on the line
for you.

07:12.570 --> 07:15.130
I promised Mrs. Carter
you´d behave, and look at you.

07:15.130 --> 07:17.230
Am I making you look stupid
in front of your missus, sir?

07:17.230 --> 07:18.630
Why do you care?

07:18.630 --> 07:20.270
You´ve split up with her.
Everyone knows it.

07:20.270 --> 07:22.330
Shall we, uh,
shall we come back to art?

07:22.330 --> 07:23.930
This way.

07:23.930 --> 07:25.900
-Get out.
-What are you doing, man?

07:25.900 --> 07:28.100
Get out of my sight!
Now!

07:28.100 --> 07:29.970
I´m done with you.

07:29.970 --> 07:30.900
Go!

07:31.770 --> 07:33.170
Come on.

07:33.900 --> 07:35.900
-[ Door slams ]
-Are you mad?

07:35.900 --> 07:37.500
Squaring up to a teacher
like that.

07:37.500 --> 07:39.570
After all the trouble
you´ve been in here.

07:39.570 --> 07:40.730
And you know what Dad would do.

07:40.730 --> 07:42.900
Yeah.
He´d pick your side.

07:42.900 --> 07:43.730
What side?

07:48.670 --> 07:51.900
What were that with you
and Candice down in the canteen?

07:51.900 --> 07:54.300
She mouthing on about your kid?

07:54.300 --> 07:57.630
What´s she want, money?

07:57.630 --> 07:59.230
´Cause you know she´s got to
prove it´s yours

07:59.230 --> 08:00.770
before she gets anything
from you.

08:00.770 --> 08:02.700
Don´t let her be
taking advantage of you.

08:02.700 --> 08:04.430
She just said she´s only been
with me.

08:04.430 --> 08:05.700
That´s all.

08:06.670 --> 08:08.570
Yeah. Well, she´s a liar.

08:09.370 --> 08:10.370
How would you know?

08:10.370 --> 08:12.730
She´s a liar, Jordan.
Don´t be stupid.

08:13.900 --> 08:15.900
Did you sleep with her?

08:15.900 --> 08:18.270
[ Exhales sharply ]
With Candice?

08:18.270 --> 08:20.900
Give me some respect, Jordan.

08:20.900 --> 08:21.900
Why?

08:21.900 --> 08:23.630
What did she say?

08:23.630 --> 08:26.330
[ Down-tempo music plays ]

08:26.330 --> 08:28.230
Said you´re Jamie´s dad.

08:33.230 --> 08:35.770
Come on.
Let´s go home.

08:36.470 --> 08:38.070
Well, you didn´t, did you?

08:39.630 --> 08:41.070
Well, did you?

08:41.070 --> 08:42.330
Come on.

08:42.330 --> 08:43.930
You know I liked her.

08:50.670 --> 08:53.570
I said you shouldn´t trust her.

08:53.570 --> 08:55.100
Okay?

08:55.100 --> 08:57.170
[ Music continues ]

08:58.500 --> 09:00.700
I didn´t know
you´d been with her!

09:01.630 --> 09:03.970
She said she liked me!

09:04.970 --> 09:07.230
[ Horns playing off-key ]

09:13.070 --> 09:15.070
[ Music ends, applause ]

09:18.030 --> 09:18.970
MANDY:
Thanks.

09:18.970 --> 09:22.030
That´s just a sample of some
of the musical opportunities

09:22.030 --> 09:23.130
here at the school.

09:23.130 --> 09:25.530
And now for an insider´s view

09:25.530 --> 09:27.130
of life here
at Ackley Bridge College,

09:27.130 --> 09:30.430
I´d like to pass you over
to our sponsor´s daughter

09:30.430 --> 09:33.330
and sixth former here,
Alya Nawaz.

09:33.330 --> 09:35.970
-Do us proud.
-[ Applause ]

09:42.300 --> 09:44.370
ALYA:
My name is Alya Nawaz.

09:44.900 --> 09:48.100
At my last school, only 10%
of the pupils were white,

09:48.100 --> 09:51.670
so when I heard about
this new school, I was excited.

09:51.670 --> 09:54.730
I was excited because it was
an opportunity to study

09:54.730 --> 09:58.570
and to make friends with a new
and diverse group of people.

10:02.500 --> 10:04.970
We were meant to...

10:04.970 --> 10:06.900
We were meant to integrate.

10:06.900 --> 10:09.470
[ Down-tempo music plays ]

10:09.470 --> 10:11.470
We were meant to make friends...

10:12.770 --> 10:15.730
...and we were meant to be
a success story.

10:17.230 --> 10:18.700
But we´re not.

10:18.700 --> 10:21.900
The only thing that´s been
successful has been my dad.

10:21.900 --> 10:23.670
My dad´s screwing
the headmistress.

10:23.670 --> 10:26.170
That´s the only bit
of integration going on here.

10:26.170 --> 10:28.900
[ Audience murmuring ]

10:39.330 --> 10:39.970
Mum.

10:43.630 --> 10:45.900
Hey, Missy.
You all right?

10:47.270 --> 10:48.530
How´s your mum?

10:48.530 --> 10:49.900
Mm.
Feeling rough.

10:49.900 --> 10:52.270
She´s worried
about the care hearing.

10:52.270 --> 10:53.900
Well, it´s gonna be hard.

10:53.900 --> 10:56.670
It´s quite difficult on her,
and there´s no guarantees.

10:56.670 --> 10:58.230
Ta.

10:58.230 --> 10:59.130
Mum?

10:59.130 --> 11:00.400
One minute, Chlo.

11:01.400 --> 11:03.200
I-I need to go anyway.

11:03.200 --> 11:05.130
I´ll be there
at the hearing tomorrow.

11:05.130 --> 11:06.670
I just need to see Ms. Carter.

11:06.670 --> 11:07.900
Like she cares.

11:07.900 --> 11:10.270
Hayley in care is her fault
anyway.

11:12.270 --> 11:13.570
SAMI:
Hey, Emma.

11:13.570 --> 11:16.100
Sami.
Have you seen Steve?

11:16.100 --> 11:18.730
It´s true, isn´t it --
Mandy and Mr. Nawaz?

11:18.730 --> 11:21.230
-How long are you gonna be?
-I don´t know. Why?

11:21.230 --> 11:22.930
´Cause you might have a surprise
at home.

11:22.930 --> 11:23.630
Oh.

11:23.630 --> 11:26.270
Oh, well, I´d better
hurry back, then, eh?

11:27.130 --> 11:28.730
Look, can we grab a coffee
or something?

11:28.730 --> 11:30.030
´Cause we need talk.

11:30.030 --> 11:31.670
I don´t think we should, do you?

11:34.370 --> 11:37.730
Anyway, I´ve got to go
and see the headmistress.

11:43.700 --> 11:45.570
Mandy.

11:45.670 --> 11:47.230
Mandy.

11:47.230 --> 11:48.930
I need to get back out there.

11:48.930 --> 11:50.230
Listen, Mandy.

11:50.230 --> 11:51.630
I´m sorry
that I didn´t listen to you

11:51.630 --> 11:53.030
about Jordan being a liability
down there.

11:53.030 --> 11:56.100
I´m -- I´m just --
I´m sorry about everything.

11:56.100 --> 11:57.730
Thanks.

11:57.730 --> 11:59.430
Mandy, please just talk to me.

11:59.430 --> 12:02.770
Steve, I´m just trying
to get through today, okay?

12:03.330 --> 12:05.570
We´re a mess.
Everything´s a mess.

12:05.570 --> 12:07.630
All right.
Okay.

12:07.630 --> 12:08.930
It´s all right.

12:10.100 --> 12:12.900
Listen.
Alya, she´s just an upset kid.

12:12.900 --> 12:14.470
I don´t think
it was meant for you.

12:14.470 --> 12:15.730
I think we were just collateral.

12:15.730 --> 12:17.530
Yeah.
And my job, too?

12:17.530 --> 12:19.470
Because the governors
want to talk to me tomorrow

12:19.470 --> 12:21.130
about my future.

12:21.130 --> 12:22.300
Oh, I´m sorry.

12:22.300 --> 12:24.100
I-I can see you´re busy.

12:24.100 --> 12:25.100
Yes, Ms. Keane?

12:26.500 --> 12:28.500
I need to...

12:28.500 --> 12:30.730
I need to have
tomorrow morning off.

12:30.730 --> 12:31.900
Really?
Now?

12:31.900 --> 12:34.900
It´s Hayley Booth´s, uh,
hearing, and it´s important.

12:34.900 --> 12:36.900
I´m...gonna go.

12:40.570 --> 12:41.530
Are you okay?

12:41.530 --> 12:42.670
Yeah.

12:43.770 --> 12:45.530
I´m sorry about you two.
I-If...

12:45.530 --> 12:47.270
Look, I-I don´t need
any sympathy,

12:47.270 --> 12:50.030
but what I do need is a bit more
support from my staff, you know?

12:50.030 --> 12:52.900
Like not springing time off
on me after everything.

12:52.900 --> 12:54.470
I know it´s bad timing.

12:54.470 --> 12:58.330
But Missy needs someone in there
with her, and I´m her teacher,

12:58.330 --> 13:00.170
and that´s what we´re here for,
isn´t it?

13:00.970 --> 13:03.200
No. No.

13:03.200 --> 13:05.430
What we´re here for
is to get students in

13:05.430 --> 13:08.270
to educate them
and do the best we can.

13:08.270 --> 13:10.530
And private lives
shouldn´t come into it.

13:17.230 --> 13:19.930
[ Mid-tempo music plays ]

13:21.370 --> 13:22.170
Mum?

13:22.170 --> 13:24.570
Oh, love,
I wanted to surprise you.

13:27.130 --> 13:28.900
How much have you spent
on all this?

13:28.900 --> 13:31.530
But it´s for Hayley.
For tomorrow.

13:31.530 --> 13:35.430
Plus social worker will see --
see I´m not useless.

13:35.430 --> 13:37.530
And you´re doing
your stuff at school.

13:37.530 --> 13:40.270
We´re regular model citizens,
us.

13:40.270 --> 13:42.300
All this stuff.

13:42.300 --> 13:44.100
Not got the hang of it yet.

13:44.100 --> 13:45.230
[ Sniffs ]

13:45.230 --> 13:47.130
-Oh, no!
-Oh!

13:47.130 --> 13:48.430
Don´t tell me
I´ve ruined another one.

13:48.430 --> 13:50.970
Oh, don´t worry.
Don´t worry.

13:50.970 --> 13:52.370
Quick!

13:52.370 --> 13:53.730
We can scrape off
the burnt bits.

13:53.730 --> 13:56.070
[ Voice breaking ]
Forget it! I messed it up!

13:56.070 --> 13:57.670
[ Sighs ]

13:58.900 --> 14:01.700
I can´t concentrate!

14:01.700 --> 14:03.000
I feel awful!

14:04.400 --> 14:06.530
Methadone makes it no better.

14:06.530 --> 14:08.730
[ Sobs ]

14:08.730 --> 14:12.170
Social won´t let Hayley
come back to this.

14:12.700 --> 14:14.530
CHLOE:
Your surprise is almost ready.

14:14.530 --> 14:17.130
I´m so sorry, Chlo, but can we
put it on hold for tonight?

14:17.130 --> 14:19.630
I really need to go
and see Missy Booth.

14:19.630 --> 14:21.500
Missy?
Again?

14:21.500 --> 14:23.670
Chloe, you know what´s going on
with her family.

14:23.670 --> 14:25.370
And I just feel
I need to do something.

14:25.370 --> 14:27.630
She hasn´t really got
anyone else.

14:27.630 --> 14:29.100
[ Down-tempo music plays ]

14:29.100 --> 14:30.170
Yeah.
Okay.

14:30.170 --> 14:31.730
You sure?

14:31.730 --> 14:34.130
Yeah. Course.
It can wait, this.

14:34.130 --> 14:36.270
Probably better overnight
anyway.

14:36.270 --> 14:37.330
What is it?

14:38.030 --> 14:40.070
Don´t worry.
Go and see Missy.

14:40.070 --> 14:41.700
You´re a star.
Thank you very much.

14:41.700 --> 14:43.570
Okay.
Bye.

14:43.570 --> 14:45.970
[ Music continues ]

14:45.970 --> 14:48.370
[ Cellphone beeps ]

14:54.030 --> 14:56.430
[ Vehicle approaching,
horn honking ]

15:01.130 --> 15:03.000
[ Birds chirping ]

15:03.000 --> 15:05.430
[ Horn blaring ]

15:11.100 --> 15:12.470
What are you doing?

15:12.470 --> 15:14.670
I thought I´d come see you.

15:17.170 --> 15:19.070
Whose car is that?

15:20.230 --> 15:21.330
Mr. Bell´s.

15:21.330 --> 15:24.530
[ Up-tempo music plays ]

15:24.530 --> 15:26.900
-[ Engine revving ]
-CHLOE: [ Screams ] Oh, my gosh!

15:26.900 --> 15:29.070
Jordan, no.
Jordan, don´t. Don´t!

15:29.070 --> 15:30.770
It´s -- It´s --

15:30.770 --> 15:32.430
Oh, my God, Jordan.
Jordan --

15:32.430 --> 15:36.530
[ Screams, gasps ]

15:36.530 --> 15:38.300
Jordan, are you crazy?

15:38.300 --> 15:40.570
Jordan!
[ Screams ]

15:40.570 --> 15:42.670
-[ Engine revving ]
-Stop it now. Jordan, stop it.

15:42.670 --> 15:46.070
It´s not funny.
[ Gasps ] Oh, my...

15:46.070 --> 15:47.270
Oh! Aah!

15:47.270 --> 15:49.330
[ Screams ]

15:49.330 --> 15:51.500
[ Birds squawking in distance ]

15:51.500 --> 15:53.370
Should have brought some booze.

15:53.370 --> 15:55.930
Yeah.
I didn´t think.

15:55.930 --> 15:58.970
Don´t want a repeat
of your party, though, do we?

15:58.970 --> 16:00.630
We could drive down
and get some.

16:00.630 --> 16:03.530
No. I´m not going
back down there again.

16:03.530 --> 16:05.530
What do you mean?

16:05.530 --> 16:07.030
Running away, innit?

16:08.300 --> 16:10.100
Running away?

16:18.670 --> 16:20.900
What happened with that girl
in the canteen?

16:23.770 --> 16:25.300
Naught to do with you.

16:26.170 --> 16:28.270
She´s your kid´s mum, isn´t she?

16:32.570 --> 16:33.900
It´s not my kid.

16:38.970 --> 16:40.270
That´s good.

16:42.070 --> 16:43.770
Who wants a kid at our age
anyway?

16:43.770 --> 16:46.170
[ Down-tempo music plays ]

16:52.470 --> 16:54.370
Do you want to come with me?

16:54.370 --> 16:55.470
What?

16:55.470 --> 16:57.430
Running away, like.

16:58.170 --> 16:59.470
You hate it here, don´t you?

17:02.530 --> 17:04.430
Yeah, I guess.

17:05.800 --> 17:07.230
So you should come.

17:14.300 --> 17:16.230
[ Music continues ]

17:16.230 --> 17:17.500
Ms. Keane.

17:20.770 --> 17:23.900
EMMA: Missy said
you were feeling a bit rough,

17:23.900 --> 17:25.230
having a bad time of it.

17:25.230 --> 17:27.770
Yeah.
It´s a real mystery.

17:31.130 --> 17:33.530
You need to get out.
Both of you.

17:33.530 --> 17:35.570
No need to tackle the kitchen.

17:36.570 --> 17:38.900
Try for a bit of normality.

17:38.900 --> 17:41.230
[ Mid-tempo music plays ]

17:41.230 --> 17:42.900
[ Indistinct conversations ]

17:42.900 --> 17:44.570
So are you gonna buy me
a pint, Miss?

17:44.570 --> 17:47.130
Uh, no.
I think not tonight.

17:47.130 --> 17:50.100
Aw.
What about me mum, then?

17:50.100 --> 17:51.900
Uh, tell you what.

17:51.900 --> 17:53.330
Why don´t you give them this?

17:53.330 --> 17:55.300
Tell them we want some food.
Set a tab.

17:55.300 --> 17:57.030
And I´ll have a Coke
and one for your mum.

17:57.030 --> 17:58.670
And whatever you want.

18:01.100 --> 18:03.130
-MAN: Do you need anything?
-Can I help you?

18:04.370 --> 18:05.500
Sure?

18:05.500 --> 18:06.470
Yeah.

18:08.370 --> 18:09.330
Who were that?

18:09.330 --> 18:11.230
You don´t want to know.

18:12.100 --> 18:14.500
Can´t go anywhere in this town
to get away from it.

18:14.500 --> 18:15.770
You´re doing really well.

18:16.500 --> 18:18.530
Yeah, right, I am.

18:18.530 --> 18:20.900
Burnt a cake.
Dealers coming up to me.

18:21.970 --> 18:24.100
Everyone can see
I´m a rubbish mum.

18:24.100 --> 18:25.900
No, they can´t.

18:25.900 --> 18:27.470
Easy for you to say.

18:27.470 --> 18:28.570
Oh, Christ.

18:28.570 --> 18:30.900
Are we gonna have
a rubbish-mum-off?

18:30.900 --> 18:35.170
My daughter turned up at school
drunk first day of term,

18:35.170 --> 18:38.170
then threw up in my lesson.

18:38.170 --> 18:39.130
For real?

18:39.130 --> 18:41.370
In front of my boss.

18:42.670 --> 18:44.070
None of us know
what we´re doing.

18:44.070 --> 18:47.300
We´ve just got to try.
And God knows you´re trying.

18:47.300 --> 18:48.730
MISSY:
All right?

18:48.730 --> 18:49.530
Yeah.

18:52.430 --> 18:55.030
[ Down-tempo music plays ]

19:01.430 --> 19:04.370
RIZ: Making a show of us
in front of the whole school.

19:04.370 --> 19:06.630
ALYA: So we´re just gonna
let him get away with it,

19:06.630 --> 19:08.070
lying to everyone?

19:08.070 --> 19:09.370
He deserves it.

19:09.370 --> 19:12.370
He deserves to be humiliated.

19:12.370 --> 19:14.770
He´s not the only one who´s been
humiliated, though, is he?

19:14.770 --> 19:16.430
Can I talk to you both?

19:16.430 --> 19:18.230
No. It´s a bit late for talking,
isn´t it?

19:18.230 --> 19:20.900
-Riz.
-I´m going to check on Mum.

19:22.900 --> 19:25.070
So now we´re gonna pretend
like nothing´s happened,

19:25.070 --> 19:26.700
even if it´s all a front?

19:26.700 --> 19:28.370
What´s the front?

19:28.370 --> 19:30.230
The business
I´ve worked hard for?

19:30.230 --> 19:32.530
The school I believe in?

19:32.530 --> 19:33.900
The family that I love?

19:33.900 --> 19:35.470
The marriage you´ve cheated on.

19:37.530 --> 19:39.500
There´s things
you don´t understand.

19:39.500 --> 19:40.900
There´s -- [ Sighs ]

19:40.900 --> 19:42.330
I don´t have to explain
my marriage to you.

19:42.330 --> 19:44.230
It´s not even the first time,
is it?

19:45.100 --> 19:48.270
Am I the only stupid one in this
family that believed in you?

19:48.270 --> 19:49.500
Nothing´s changed.

19:49.500 --> 19:51.230
Everything´s changed.

19:52.900 --> 19:54.970
I thought you were amazing.

19:56.900 --> 19:59.670
[ Down-tempo music plays ]

20:08.330 --> 20:10.570
[ Cellphone ringing ]

20:14.570 --> 20:15.470
Hey.

20:15.470 --> 20:16.900
Someone´s nicked my car.

20:16.900 --> 20:18.330
What?
Oh, my God.

20:18.330 --> 20:19.370
Have you called the police?

20:19.370 --> 20:22.070
Yeah, of course.
I just, um...I´m sorry.

20:22.070 --> 20:23.570
I would have called you earlier.
It´s just...

20:23.570 --> 20:25.270
No.
It´s okay.

20:25.270 --> 20:27.900
I was --
I was gonna call you, too.

20:27.900 --> 20:31.070
Just to say thanks, you know,
for today, and for --

20:31.070 --> 20:32.170
[ Computer chimes ]

20:32.170 --> 20:34.700
Um...Uh, can I --

20:34.700 --> 20:36.100
Can I just deal with
this e-mail?

20:36.100 --> 20:37.130
It´s from the governors.

20:37.130 --> 20:39.430
Can I call you back?

20:39.430 --> 20:42.170
Yeah. Yeah, yeah.
Of course.

20:42.170 --> 20:44.730
Right.
Well, I´ll speak to you later.

20:44.730 --> 20:45.700
Bye.

20:45.700 --> 20:46.930
Okay. Bye.
Bye.

20:46.930 --> 20:49.330
[ Down-tempo music plays ]

20:50.370 --> 20:53.270
[ Birds chirping,
dog barking in distance ]

21:01.170 --> 21:03.570
[ Up-tempo music playing ]

21:03.570 --> 21:06.030
CHLOE:
Are we gonna get cold?

21:06.030 --> 21:07.300
JORDAN:
You what?

21:07.300 --> 21:11.270
Sleeping up here, aren´t we?
Or do you want to drive?

21:11.270 --> 21:12.770
We can´t sleep here, can we?

21:13.700 --> 21:16.470
Why not?
You shouldn´t drive in the dark.

21:16.470 --> 21:17.700
It´s dangerous.

21:17.700 --> 21:20.430
-[ Chuckles ]
-What? Stop it.

21:20.430 --> 21:22.130
My mum hates driving
in the dark.

21:22.130 --> 21:23.300
She won´t do it.

21:23.900 --> 21:25.170
Your mum´s not here, is she?

21:27.130 --> 21:28.900
No one is.

21:30.670 --> 21:31.930
Yeah.

21:36.100 --> 21:38.170
[ Door closes ]

21:38.900 --> 21:40.430
Chloe?

21:40.430 --> 21:42.500
[ Clock ticking ]

21:44.770 --> 21:47.430
[ Down-tempo music plays ]

21:49.570 --> 21:52.230
[ Mid-tempo music plays ]

22:08.100 --> 22:11.170
I´ve...never...

22:12.170 --> 22:14.370
Never...

22:17.370 --> 22:18.570
No.

22:22.770 --> 22:25.900
I thought all you Londoners
were cool.

22:28.270 --> 22:30.530
Well, it´s not like
I couldn´t have if I wanted to.

22:30.530 --> 22:32.370
What, so you don´t want to?

22:35.130 --> 22:39.670
You said...that you wanted
to run away with me.

22:39.670 --> 22:41.770
So that means
I´ve got to sleep with you?

22:44.070 --> 22:46.370
[ Down-tempo music plays ]

23:04.000 --> 23:05.770
You all right?

23:08.900 --> 23:11.070
I just want to leave this place.

23:11.700 --> 23:14.170
I hate it here.
I hate the people.

23:19.470 --> 23:21.300
I hate you, Ackley Bridge!

23:31.770 --> 23:33.700
[ Music continues ]

23:47.170 --> 23:49.100
I didn´t know who else to call.

23:49.100 --> 23:50.330
It´s all right.

23:50.330 --> 23:51.730
I mean, maybe she´s out
with her friends,

23:51.730 --> 23:54.470
but she did all this,
and said she´d be here and...

23:54.470 --> 23:56.270
It´s fine.

23:59.470 --> 24:01.500
[ Exhales deeply ]

24:20.170 --> 24:23.470
We...We can´t do this.

24:23.470 --> 24:24.900
You´ve got a fiancée.

24:24.900 --> 24:26.170
I met her. She´s nice.

24:26.170 --> 24:27.570
-She´s good for you. You said...
-I-I know.

24:27.570 --> 24:30.500
This is the worst timing ever,
but...

24:36.070 --> 24:37.900
We just need to find Chloe.

24:39.670 --> 24:41.970
[ Music continues ]

24:48.630 --> 24:51.070
SIMONE:
I´m sorry, Missy.

24:51.070 --> 24:53.170
I´ve let you down so much.

25:15.670 --> 25:18.070
[ Dog barking in distance ]

25:24.470 --> 25:26.570
[ Knock on window ]

25:30.500 --> 25:32.430
[ Up-tempo music plays ]

25:32.430 --> 25:34.130
Mum?

25:36.700 --> 25:37.970
Mum?

25:48.470 --> 25:49.900
[ Birds chirping ]

25:49.900 --> 25:52.470
[ Cellphone ringing, buzzing ]

25:55.530 --> 25:56.330
Hello?

25:56.770 --> 25:57.570
Yes.

25:58.470 --> 26:00.630
Yeah.
She´s at the station now?

26:00.630 --> 26:01.970
And she´s all right?

26:01.970 --> 26:04.330
No. I´ll come straightaway.
Thank you. Thank you very much.

26:04.330 --> 26:05.300
Bye-bye.
Bye.

26:06.330 --> 26:09.570
Asleep in a stolen car
halfway up the valley.

26:09.570 --> 26:11.630
-You want me to take you?
-No. No. You´ve done enough.

26:11.630 --> 26:13.030
Thank you so much.

26:13.030 --> 26:14.730
I´d have gone crazy
without you here.

26:19.670 --> 26:22.230
I don´t want to break up
a couple, Sami.

26:24.100 --> 26:26.770
And I don´t want to mess around.

26:45.100 --> 26:47.770
No. I´ve got to go
and get Chloe, haven´t I?

26:50.430 --> 26:51.370
See you.

26:52.730 --> 26:55.070
[ Cellphone rings ]

26:55.070 --> 26:56.370
Hi, Emma.

26:56.370 --> 26:57.900
I can´t make it to the hearing.

26:57.900 --> 26:59.170
What hearing?

26:59.170 --> 27:00.800
Hayley Booth´s.

27:00.800 --> 27:02.970
I´ve got to go and get Chloe
from the police station.

27:02.970 --> 27:04.000
The police?

27:04.000 --> 27:05.800
She went missing last night.

27:05.800 --> 27:09.070
But...Missy needs someone there.

27:09.070 --> 27:11.470
I just hate to think of her
on her own, Mandy.

27:11.470 --> 27:14.670
Her mother´s still a right state
and if she loses a sister...

27:14.670 --> 27:15.900
-[ Doorbell rings ]
-God.

27:15.900 --> 27:18.470
I know what you´re asking,
but I can´t go for you.

27:18.470 --> 27:20.530
She´s 16 years old.

27:20.530 --> 27:22.900
Look, I´ve -- I´ve got a meeting
with the governors.

27:22.900 --> 27:24.270
She´ll just have to go
on her own.

27:24.270 --> 27:26.500
And you´d better deal
with your daughter.

27:29.030 --> 27:31.100
Um...

27:31.100 --> 27:32.470
I´ve got to go.

27:34.900 --> 27:36.300
[ Exhales deeply ]

27:36.900 --> 27:37.670
Sorry.

27:38.430 --> 27:39.630
What are you doing?

27:39.630 --> 27:42.230
I just came to wish you luck --
for the meeting.

27:43.700 --> 27:45.230
Right.

27:45.230 --> 27:47.770
If Sadiq´s got any decency,
he´ll resign.

27:48.500 --> 27:49.900
Or I will.

27:49.900 --> 27:51.470
Don´t you dare.

27:51.470 --> 27:53.370
You´re a great teacher.

27:55.300 --> 27:56.470
Unlike me.

27:56.470 --> 27:57.530
What do you mean?

27:57.530 --> 27:59.970
Jordan Wilson. It turns out
he´s the famous car thief.

27:59.970 --> 28:01.770
They found it.

28:01.770 --> 28:04.170
Gonna go and get it now.
The taxi´s outside.

28:04.770 --> 28:06.170
I was driving past,
and I just...

28:06.170 --> 28:08.730
Steve, you´re a great teacher.

28:08.730 --> 28:11.770
I´m sorry
if I ever made you doubt it.

28:11.770 --> 28:13.070
What´s the point in a school

28:13.070 --> 28:14.900
if you don´t care
about the people in it?

28:16.130 --> 28:17.900
Well, you care too.

28:19.270 --> 28:21.170
One of the reasons
why I love you.

28:24.730 --> 28:26.570
Do you still love me, then?

28:27.700 --> 28:30.430
It was never about me
not loving you, was it?

28:31.670 --> 28:33.030
I know.

28:40.630 --> 28:41.900
I´ve got this meeting.

28:41.900 --> 28:43.900
Yeah.

28:43.900 --> 28:45.070
Well, share my cab.

28:45.070 --> 28:48.700
I mean, it´s in
the same direction, so...

28:49.770 --> 28:50.900
Is it?

28:52.070 --> 28:53.030
No.

28:53.530 --> 28:54.630
No.

29:00.370 --> 29:02.770
[ Mid-tempo music plays ]

29:31.770 --> 29:33.770
[ Birds chirping ]

29:36.630 --> 29:38.530
[ Engine shuts off ]

29:46.500 --> 29:49.730
[ Up-tempo music plays ]

29:51.130 --> 29:54.130
Actually, can we go back
into town, please?

29:54.130 --> 29:55.230
You´re gonna be late.

29:56.100 --> 29:57.670
I should be somewhere else.

29:57.670 --> 30:00.170
[ Engine starts ]

30:03.700 --> 30:05.970
Oh, are they back together again
happy?

30:05.970 --> 30:08.070
SAMI:
Well, hopefully, yeah.

30:08.070 --> 30:10.030
You still engaged?

30:10.030 --> 30:10.900
Yep.

30:10.900 --> 30:12.330
Still liaising?

30:12.330 --> 30:13.370
Yeah.

30:13.370 --> 30:16.270
You know you´re wearing
same jumper as yesterday?

30:16.270 --> 30:18.070
[ Mid-tempo music plays ]

30:18.070 --> 30:20.030
Hashtag just saying.

30:24.570 --> 30:27.100
Nas, can I talk to you?

30:30.330 --> 30:31.900
Yesterday, in class --

30:31.900 --> 30:34.170
Anyone could have found out, the
way you two were carrying on.

30:34.170 --> 30:35.900
Oh, we were only joking.

30:35.900 --> 30:37.130
It´s not a joke.

30:38.030 --> 30:39.570
It´s not a joke to me.

30:40.330 --> 30:42.330
Look, I should never
have gone near you.

30:42.330 --> 30:43.970
I know.
You have said that before.

30:43.970 --> 30:45.700
No.
You don´t understand.

30:45.700 --> 30:47.570
I should never have gone
near you.

30:47.570 --> 30:48.770
You´re a student.

30:48.770 --> 30:50.030
I´m 17.

30:50.030 --> 30:51.730
My student.

30:51.730 --> 30:53.230
I´m here to be trusted.

30:54.030 --> 30:54.970
I let you down.

30:54.970 --> 30:56.930
Look, you broke the rules.
Big deal.

30:56.930 --> 30:59.300
-That´s what they´re there for.
-They´re there to protect you.

30:59.300 --> 31:01.500
Protect me?
From you?

31:02.970 --> 31:04.300
Yeah.

31:04.970 --> 31:06.300
Look, I...

31:08.770 --> 31:10.330
...I am over it.

31:11.170 --> 31:13.630
So you don´t have to worry
anymore.

31:13.630 --> 31:15.970
Look, I´m not gonna say
anything,

31:15.970 --> 31:17.630
and I´m not gonna tell anyone.

31:18.930 --> 31:20.270
I promise you.

31:21.900 --> 31:23.370
It´s done.

31:26.530 --> 31:28.900
I´m hoping I´m gonna see you
in a minute.

31:28.900 --> 31:31.430
But please get back to me
when you get this message.

31:34.930 --> 31:35.900
Hayley!

31:41.630 --> 31:42.430
Where´s Mum?

31:45.130 --> 31:47.370
She´s trying to get hold of her.

31:50.670 --> 31:51.930
Ms. Carter?

31:51.930 --> 31:54.100
All right, girls.
Ms. Keane couldn´t make it.

31:54.100 --> 31:56.170
I thought you could do
with some school support, so...

31:57.670 --> 32:00.130
...let´s see if we can
get you home, Hayley.

32:00.130 --> 32:02.300
[ Cellphone ringing ]

32:02.300 --> 32:04.200
[ Indistinct conversations ]

32:04.200 --> 32:05.400
Mum.

32:05.900 --> 32:08.030
Oh.
[ Exhales deeply ]

32:08.900 --> 32:10.930
I didn´t mean to scare you.

32:10.930 --> 32:12.370
You didn´t come home.

32:12.900 --> 32:14.630
You didn´t answer your phone.

32:14.630 --> 32:17.030
You said it was all right
for me to go and see Missy.

32:17.030 --> 32:19.670
Well, what´s this?
Some kind of punishment?

32:19.670 --> 32:20.930
No.
It´s just...

32:20.930 --> 32:22.330
Jordan turned up --

32:22.330 --> 32:24.430
My job´s really important
to me, Chloe.

32:26.100 --> 32:27.370
Yeah.

32:28.030 --> 32:30.030
I know it´s the most important
thing to you, Mum.

32:30.030 --> 32:32.300
I get that.
I get the message.

32:34.570 --> 32:36.370
I´m not having a go.
I´m...

32:39.630 --> 32:42.230
I just don´t understand
why you didn´t come home.

32:43.730 --> 32:44.730
Home?

32:46.170 --> 32:49.500
Is that my home or -- or is my
home back in London with Dad?

32:49.500 --> 32:51.470
If Dad hadn´t dumped me here,
we´d --

32:51.470 --> 32:53.700
we´d still be
every other weekend.

32:54.900 --> 32:57.730
Like, always doing something...
fun.

32:57.730 --> 33:00.330
Oh. Well, I´m sorry
for trying to spoil you.

33:00.330 --> 33:02.800
I don´t want spoiling.

33:03.830 --> 33:05.430
[ Sighs ]
I just...

33:07.470 --> 33:09.670
I want my mum.

33:11.130 --> 33:13.730
I always feel like I´m...
in your way.

33:13.730 --> 33:16.430
It -- I mean...

33:16.430 --> 33:20.670
What´s up here that you couldn´t
have had back in London with me?

33:23.370 --> 33:24.670
I just...

33:25.700 --> 33:28.900
I didn´t think I´d be any good
as a full-time parent.

33:28.900 --> 33:33.970
I-I thought I´d be better
as a part-time mum, and, um...

33:35.370 --> 33:38.270
...it seems I´m right.

33:38.900 --> 33:40.970
Well, Dad doesn´t want me
anymore.

33:44.070 --> 33:46.230
He does.
He does.

33:46.770 --> 33:49.230
And I want you.

33:49.230 --> 33:53.070
But I want you more
and he´s not getting you back.

33:53.070 --> 33:54.500
You´re all mine now.

33:54.500 --> 33:56.570
[ Down-tempo music plays ]

33:58.530 --> 34:00.500
Oh, Chloe.

34:05.330 --> 34:07.730
[ Indistinct conversations,
telephones ringing ]

34:12.070 --> 34:13.900
I´m sure my mum will be here
in a minute.

34:13.900 --> 34:14.770
She promised.

34:14.770 --> 34:17.500
WOMAN:
Can we have the Booths, please?

34:17.500 --> 34:18.900
DARREN:
They´re calling us in.

34:18.900 --> 34:20.530
The best we can do
is get an adjournment

34:20.530 --> 34:22.300
and maybe your mum will have
a good explanation.

34:23.300 --> 34:25.270
Uh, just family is usual.

34:25.270 --> 34:26.330
Well, we´ll be unusual.

34:26.330 --> 34:28.270
Uh, Missy,
you need to give permission

34:28.270 --> 34:30.230
if you want Mrs. Carter
to join you.

34:30.230 --> 34:32.300
I can ask her to wait outside.

34:33.070 --> 34:34.700
Come if you want.

34:35.970 --> 34:38.900
Let´s see if we can buy
your mum some time, shall we?

34:38.900 --> 34:40.900
[ Mid-tempo music plays ]

34:42.530 --> 34:44.900
[ Indistinct talking on radio ]

34:44.900 --> 34:46.900
-Cheers. Thank you.
-Yep.

34:49.930 --> 34:51.230
They said I could say hello.

34:55.430 --> 34:57.970
So, what was the plan, Jordan?

35:02.400 --> 35:04.100
I don´t know, sir.

35:05.330 --> 35:07.130
I never really have a plan,
do I?

35:09.630 --> 35:12.970
You were getting it together
at school.

35:12.970 --> 35:14.570
And I was...

35:17.100 --> 35:18.900
...I was proud of you, you know?

35:18.900 --> 35:20.100
Now you go and do something
like this?

35:20.100 --> 35:21.700
I know.

35:25.230 --> 35:30.030
Jordan...you´ve got a kid
to think about.

35:31.930 --> 35:34.170
Candice said it´s not mine.

35:34.170 --> 35:35.770
It´s Cory´s.

35:38.270 --> 35:39.430
Y-Your Cory´s?

35:39.430 --> 35:40.370
Yeah.

35:41.900 --> 35:43.770
[ Down-tempo music plays ]

35:43.770 --> 35:45.930
What about the DNA test?

35:47.170 --> 35:48.530
I lied.

35:49.430 --> 35:51.300
Oh, Christ.

35:55.270 --> 35:57.530
Oh, I´m so sorry, Jordan.

36:02.730 --> 36:04.970
[ Indistinct conversations ]

36:04.970 --> 36:07.300
[ Dog barking in distance ]

36:07.300 --> 36:09.330
[ Music continues ]

36:25.270 --> 36:26.570
All right?

36:27.470 --> 36:29.170
I...

36:43.770 --> 36:44.900
Hey.

36:47.100 --> 36:48.330
Hey.

36:50.930 --> 36:52.100
Hey.

36:54.500 --> 36:56.030
Shh.

37:02.830 --> 37:04.600
I´ll just be a sec.

37:16.730 --> 37:19.900
Get to class, you.

37:21.130 --> 37:23.900
[ Door closes ]

37:24.900 --> 37:26.270
Does she know anything?

37:28.630 --> 37:30.900
Sami...

37:30.900 --> 37:32.770
I´ve got to look after her.

37:32.770 --> 37:35.130
She´s my daughter, and I´ve only
got her a couple of years,

37:35.130 --> 37:37.370
and then she´ll be off -- gone.

37:38.500 --> 37:41.270
I haven´t got room
for anything else.

37:43.330 --> 37:45.100
Well, I-I get that,
but I just don´t understand --

37:45.100 --> 37:46.500
I can´t mess this up, Sami.

37:46.500 --> 37:48.470
Look at me.

37:48.530 --> 37:49.900
Look at me.

37:52.070 --> 37:53.770
What are you scared of?

37:57.370 --> 37:59.770
Just call your fiancée.

38:00.370 --> 38:01.770
You haven´t told her anything.

38:03.530 --> 38:05.370
There´s no harm done.

38:07.300 --> 38:08.900
I´m sorry.

38:12.770 --> 38:14.700
[ Telephone ringing ]

38:18.770 --> 38:20.770
RIZ:
You gonna resign?

38:20.770 --> 38:22.670
It takes two, you know.

38:22.670 --> 38:25.230
I had to resign
from the golf club this morning,

38:25.230 --> 38:27.500
and my interview
in the newspaper got dropped.

38:27.500 --> 38:28.770
You should leave.

38:28.770 --> 38:30.530
What do you want me to do?
Just walk away?

38:30.530 --> 38:31.970
To take your punishment.

38:31.970 --> 38:34.900
Punishment?
I´m getting it. Don´t worry.

38:34.900 --> 38:36.730
From your mother.
From your sister.

38:36.730 --> 38:38.500
From you.

38:38.500 --> 38:41.270
I´m not going down
without a fight, son.

38:41.270 --> 38:42.500
Why should I?

38:42.500 --> 38:45.370
Because you slept
with the headmistress, Dad.

38:46.330 --> 38:48.270
Mr. Nawaz, you can go up now.

38:48.270 --> 38:50.130
They´re ready for you.

38:50.670 --> 38:53.900
It doesn´t look like Mrs. Carter
is gonna turn up.

38:59.130 --> 39:01.970
If Ms. Booth isn´t here,
I have no choice.

39:01.970 --> 39:03.570
[ Clears throat ]

39:04.130 --> 39:06.170
I am Missy and Hayley´s
head teacher...

39:06.170 --> 39:07.630
Mrs. Carter.

39:07.630 --> 39:09.900
...and -- and I think
it´s really important

39:09.900 --> 39:11.300
for them to stay together.

39:11.300 --> 39:13.970
Um, Hayley has made
excellent progress,

39:13.970 --> 39:15.730
and interfering
with her education...

39:15.730 --> 39:17.270
-I know you´re trying to help --
-...at this point

39:17.270 --> 39:19.470
would be hugely detrimental.

39:19.470 --> 39:22.030
And Missy --
Missy is an excellent student.

39:22.030 --> 39:25.300
I mean, she has overcome
all sorts of difficulties,

39:25.300 --> 39:28.070
and she´s made us all
really proud.

39:28.930 --> 39:31.270
This year, she´s got
a whole new attitude --

39:31.270 --> 39:33.430
Not that there was anything
wrong with her attitude before.

39:33.430 --> 39:35.770
You were fine when we were
living with Nana before.

39:35.770 --> 39:36.630
That´s enough.

39:36.630 --> 39:39.030
But we were looking after Nana
rather than other way round.

39:39.030 --> 39:40.570
And we coped.
We were happy.

39:41.170 --> 39:42.930
We might not be
the kind of family

39:42.930 --> 39:44.670
social workers give
top marks to,

39:44.670 --> 39:46.100
but we were good!

39:46.100 --> 39:47.900
And we were together!

39:50.300 --> 39:52.230
JUDGE: I do understand
your distress, Missy,

39:52.230 --> 39:54.170
but with the absence
of your mother --

39:54.170 --> 39:55.730
[ Door opens ]

39:55.730 --> 39:58.900
[ Exhales sharply ]
Buses were a nightmare.

39:58.900 --> 40:01.430
You´ve not started already,
have you?

40:01.970 --> 40:04.100
And I didn´t know
my proper size.

40:04.100 --> 40:06.300
Woman in the shop said I´ve been
wearing the wrong-sized bra

40:06.300 --> 40:08.730
for 20 years.

40:08.730 --> 40:12.230
[ Mid-tempo music plays ]

40:14.770 --> 40:16.900
My father came to this country
with naught.

40:17.670 --> 40:21.700
And I built my life,
my business from scratch.

40:21.700 --> 40:24.330
From being the wrong
side of town,

40:24.330 --> 40:27.970
from being the other,
from being the minority.

40:28.930 --> 40:31.270
I put my own money
into this place.

40:31.270 --> 40:33.530
That´s how much
I want it to work.

40:33.530 --> 40:35.630
My reputation, my --

40:35.630 --> 40:39.170
We also have to consider
the reputation of the school.

40:39.170 --> 40:42.730
What a man does in his private
life is his own business,

40:42.730 --> 40:43.900
his family´s business.

40:43.900 --> 40:47.770
Not when you´re the sponsor
of a public-funded academy.

40:48.430 --> 40:51.570
We´re grateful
for your generous donations,

40:51.570 --> 40:56.100
but if we have to find another
sponsor, you must know...

40:56.100 --> 40:59.270
that this school will survive
without you.

41:03.500 --> 41:05.130
It takes two.

41:06.300 --> 41:08.430
And I´m not the one
in charge of the kids.

41:09.130 --> 41:11.470
I´m not the one who´s gonna have
cracks made about her

41:11.470 --> 41:12.630
in the classroom,

41:12.630 --> 41:15.070
who´s gonna have problems
with discipline,

41:15.070 --> 41:18.900
who´s most likely divorcing
another member of staff.

41:18.900 --> 41:20.900
And she´s not even here!

41:21.370 --> 41:23.900
She´s not even bothered
to turn up.

41:23.900 --> 41:27.470
She´s not even here
to face the music.

41:28.730 --> 41:30.900
You reckon one of us has to go?

41:32.100 --> 41:34.030
Well, it´s not gonna be me.

41:35.100 --> 41:38.370
[ Whispering indistinctly ]

41:38.970 --> 41:41.330
-They´re taking the mick here.
-Mum.

41:43.630 --> 41:44.900
Stop that.

41:45.470 --> 41:46.970
DARREN: I think
under the circumstances,

41:46.970 --> 41:48.730
that is the best decision.

41:48.730 --> 41:50.070
All right.

41:52.300 --> 41:53.370
Right.

41:53.370 --> 41:55.330
Well, I´m sorry
to have kept you all waiting,

41:55.330 --> 41:57.500
but I can now tell you
my decision,

41:57.500 --> 41:59.900
and I´ve decided
that the right orders

41:59.900 --> 42:04.370
are a supervision order to
the local authority for a year

42:04.370 --> 42:08.770
and a child arrangements
order to Ms. Booth.

42:09.900 --> 42:12.330
Hayley, that means
you can return home

42:12.330 --> 42:14.630
to the care of your mother.

42:14.630 --> 42:16.570
-[ Laughter ]
-Yes. Yes!

42:16.570 --> 42:17.730
Sorry.

42:17.730 --> 42:19.900
Yes.
That´s great.

42:19.900 --> 42:22.130
[ Exhales deeply ]

42:22.130 --> 42:23.430
Nice one.

42:23.430 --> 42:26.130
[ Mid-tempo music plays ]

42:32.900 --> 42:35.100
Mandy not make it back in time?

42:35.100 --> 42:36.230
In time for what?

42:36.230 --> 42:37.900
What have you been saying
to them in there?

42:37.900 --> 42:39.770
Oh, do we have to do this
yet again, Mr. Bell?

42:39.770 --> 42:40.730
Listen.

42:40.730 --> 42:44.130
You know that this school is ten
times better off with her here.

42:44.700 --> 42:46.070
The board will make
their own decision.

42:46.070 --> 42:46.970
Own decision?

42:46.970 --> 42:49.370
You can´t force a woman
out of a job ´cause of this.

42:49.370 --> 42:51.100
Mandy´s going nowhere,
and neither am I.

42:51.100 --> 42:52.900
What did you say to them?

42:54.470 --> 42:56.630
Ms. Carter...

42:57.230 --> 42:59.570
...the governors will see you
after lunch now.

42:59.570 --> 43:00.970
But there´s been some sort of...

43:00.970 --> 43:01.970
What?

43:01.970 --> 43:04.430
An explosion
in the chemistry lab.

43:04.430 --> 43:06.970
Some Year 10s, apparently.

43:06.970 --> 43:09.270
If you´ll excuse me, I´d better
go and deal with this.

43:09.270 --> 43:10.970
After all, it is my school.

43:10.970 --> 43:12.170
Our school.

43:13.370 --> 43:14.630
We´ll see.

43:16.570 --> 43:19.470
[ Mid-tempo music plays ]

43:20.900 --> 43:23.130
[ Indistinct conversations ]

43:30.130 --> 43:31.470
Hayley!

43:31.470 --> 43:32.700
Raz!

43:34.670 --> 43:36.970
[ Music continues ]

43:47.130 --> 43:49.100
Come here, you.
[ Laughs ]

44:06.030 --> 44:09.030
[ Down-tempo music plays ]

44:09.030 --> 44:11.900
I can´t believe they´ve
still not got rid of this.

44:11.900 --> 44:13.900
I know.
It´s the council, innit?

44:13.900 --> 44:15.330
My mum´s dead mad about it.

44:15.330 --> 44:17.730
We gonna get in trouble
for skiving?

44:17.730 --> 44:20.170
I think they got enough
going on.

44:20.170 --> 44:22.070
They´re not gonna notice us.

44:22.070 --> 44:23.670
Not gonna no--

44:23.670 --> 44:25.370
Not gonna notice?

44:25.370 --> 44:30.430
Nasreen...we are always noticed.

44:30.430 --> 44:33.500
We are always gonna be noticed.

44:33.500 --> 44:35.770
Take note, Ackley Bridge.

44:35.770 --> 44:38.030
Note us!

44:38.030 --> 44:39.300
I´m actually gonna be sick.

44:39.300 --> 44:41.670
Oh, no, Missy.
Don´t, please.

44:41.670 --> 44:45.300
We´re gonna get in so much...

44:45.300 --> 44:47.070
-Trouble!
-...trouble!

44:47.070 --> 44:48.130
[ Both laugh ]

44:48.130 --> 44:50.900
[ Mid-tempo music plays ]
